// Reassert both ensures conjuncts in the proof context so z3 instantiates the
// (otherwise trigger-disjoint) `SingleDelivery::receive_ack` predicate for the
// two candidate post-states against the shared `pre_self_` / `pkt`. The if/else
// guard inside `receive_ack` depends only on the (pre, pkt) pair, so both runs
// take the same branch; lifting them out with an extensional `=~=` then forces
// the abstract `send_state` map to coincide between the two post-states.
assert(SingleDelivery::receive_ack(pre_self_@, post1_self_@, pkt@, set!{}));
assert(SingleDelivery::receive_ack(pre_self_@, post2_self_@, pkt@, set!{}));
assert(post1_self_@.send_state =~= post2_self_@.send_state);
